## Ferrum — MCP cancellation token

The prior rite minted a `CancellationToken` inside the MCP task that **nothing ever cancelled**, so streamable HTTP could not shut down cleanly. **Resolved:** root token in `run()`, `child_token()` wired into `StreamableHttpServerConfig`, `ctrl_c` cancels the root, Axum REST uses `with_graceful_shutdown` on the same tree. `tokio-util` is a normal dependency (not mcp-gated). *Imperator vult* — one signal, both gates.

